# Video Background Plates

Before writing or editing any Remotion composition, read `src/data/videoPlates.ts`.

This file is the registry of all available AI-generated background video plates.
Each entry includes the file path, mood description, palette hint, and pre-tuned
opacity/scrim values. Use it to decide whether to include a `VideoPlate` in the
composition you are writing.

## When to include a VideoPlate

Include a `VideoPlate` when:
- The composition is a bespoke hand-crafted ad (not a config-driven VerticalAd)
- A registry entry exists whose `suitableFor` array or `mood` description matches
  the brand/style of the composition being written
- The composition has a consistent background mood across most of its scenes

Do NOT include a VideoPlate when:
- No suitable plate exists in the registry yet (tell the user which prompt template
  from `public/video/README.md` to use to generate one)
- The composition uses Three.js / ThreeCanvas as the full background (e.g. AwesomeAd,
  CinemaRevealAd) — the 3D environment already provides the visual depth
- The composition is a config-driven ad using `GradientBackground`

## How to use

```tsx
import { VideoPlate } from "../components/VideoPlate";

// Inside the composition root AbsoluteFill, as the FIRST child:
<VideoPlate plateId="haven-warm" scrimColor={C.bg} />
```

Always set `scrimColor` to the composition's own background token (e.g. `C.bg`).
This color-grades the video plate to feel native to the palette.

## How to register a new plate

After the user drops a new MP4 into `public/video/`, add one entry to
`src/data/videoPlates.ts` following the existing pattern, then use it.

## Scrim tuning reference

| Palette type | scrimOpacity range |
|---|---|
| Light (cream, ivory, white) | 0.55–0.65 |
| Mid (warm grey, muted) | 0.45–0.55 |
| Dark (navy, black, espresso) | 0.35–0.45 |
